p: WNV-prME/SLEV.IC- immune HOSPs challenged with the reciprocal chimeric virus, SLEV-prME/WNV.IC produced daily mean titers that were not significantly different (p>0.05) from daily mean titers in naive HOSPs inoculated with SLEV-prME/WNV.IC ( Fig 4E). Peak mean titers between naïve and challenged HOSPs were not significantly different (p>0.05) ( Fig 4F). However, one HOSP (red scatter plot) developed SLEV-prME/WNV.IC titers that were significantly higher (p<0.05) than naïve HOSPs at 23, 24 and 26 dpi. Another WNV-prME/SLEV.IC- immune HOSP (orange scatter plot) also produced statistically higher SLEV-prME/WNV.IC titers at 26 dpi (p<0.05).
